Getting back in action.
.
Sup peeps!? Hope you guys are having a great week. After doing nothing but celebrating, traveling, and eating an inappropriate amount of sweets over the last week, I finally made it back home (the gym).
.
Want to touch on this quickly guys. You don’t need to sweat these small breaks where you can’t get to the gym or aren’t able to track your macros perfectly.
.
Over the long term it’s just a blip. No gains will be lost, and you can just get right back on track with your macros after the holiday season.
.
Remember, what you eat between Christmas and New Years is nothing in comparison to what you eat between New Years and Christmas.
.
Keep moving forward peeps.

🍪Why you should strap one on...
.
🦁When you use a belt, intra-abdominal pressure increases by 25% to 40% than when you lift without a weightlifting belt. This means the stress on your lower back will be greatly reduced.
.
👻You obviously don’t want to rely on the belt, but as you approach heavier weight it’s not a bad idea to throw one on.

PULL DAY WORKOUT
.
🤙Swipe through and save (saves will help more people see this so if you dig it please take a sec to save ❤️ )
.
💪Go to town on this workout if you wanna get lean or if you wanna get massive.
.
👉...FYI getting lean or bulking up will be dependent on diet not exercise selection. Your routine shouldn’t change whether your bulking or cutting. If anyone tells you otherwise cut em off.
.
Deads
5x3
Remember to keep your neck neutral don’t hyper extend
.
Wide Lat Pulldowns
3x12
Keep thumbs over bar try to “pull with your elbows)
.
Underhand barbell rows
3x10
Keep back neutral, avoid rounding
.
Straight arm pulldowns
3x10
Keep core braced don’t get lazy here
.
Ez Bar Bicep curls
100 reps however many sets you need
Like to do a burnout of bis like this with one exercise on pull days since I also have an arm day in my split.
.

Training Fasted vs Training Fed (READ 👇)
.
For the first time in a long time I trained fed today (had a meal before my workout) Unsurprisingly to me, it wasn’t a great sesh.
.
I have been training fasted (first thing in the morning) for years. I feel strongest in the morning and I’m super focused so this works best for me.
.
This is how you should approach training. How do you feel best? Fed/Fasted? What time do you feel best? AM/Midday/Evening
.
Everyone is different and there is no cookie cutter ideal for all of us. Learn to listen to your body and experiment with different times/different pre workout meals/non meals.
.
Unless you’re training to be Mr Olympia, you don’t need to worry about meal timing. It won’t impact you as much as a bad sesh at the gym will.
.
So get that mentality of “I need to eat to fuel my workout” and “I gotta eat something every 3 hours or I’ll shrivel up into a raisin” out of your head.
.
Again, for 99.99% of us this won’t have any impact on our goals, and will more than likely cause you to get super frustrated when you miss that one meal/shake whatever.
.
Keep it simple! Focus on hitting your macro target for the day, and train when/how you feel strongest. That’s it. Don’t over complicate it.
.
⭐️Stay #MOSITIVE

SET BIG GOALS (read 👇)
.
Road to a 500lb bench press started today for me with a 5x5 at 345.
.
After coming in a month early on my 405 bench press goal for 2019, I’m taking advantage of this month by looking forward to bigger things.
.
I know people will think I’m crazy for setting such a big goal and they’ll give me a million reasons why I won’t get there, but that’s just a lot of noise.
.
You are capable of so much more than you think and 10x more than what other people think.
.
For 2020 set some big goals!!!
.
Wanna lose 100lbs? Do it!
.
Wanna add 100lbs to your deadlift? Do it!
.
*** All things are possible, BUT (big fat but) you have to be willing to COMMIT EVERY DAY towards achieving that goal.
.
It’s not gonna happen in a month, or by putting in some crazy effort for two months, it’s gonna happen by CONSISTENTLY achieving your tasks day after day.
.
Keep this in mind! It’s not that one huge swing of the axe that brings the tree down it’s the thousands of small hacks over and over that get the job done.
.
Hope this motivates you guys to get your ass outta bed this Sunday! Get after it!
.
⭐️Stay #MOSITIVE

#TBT to Oct 2018 (READ👇 same rules still apply)
.
KNOW - BALANCE
-
Keeping it real today guys.
-
I’m all for hydration, not drinking liquid cals and making sure you’re getting enough water on the daily. However, that doesn’t mean you can’t go out and have a drink every now and again.
-
I’m not the biggest drinker and I really only drink on occasion, but with social events and holidays coming up (rakija aka Croatian moonshine will be flowing) I don’t mind having a drink with friends and family to celebrate with them.
-
Don’t obsess and make life all about restricting and allowing. Celebrate the day/moment with your friends and family and get back on track the next day.
-
Besides it’s bad luck to “cheers” with water.
-
⭐️ Stay #MOSITIVE

If you want more “luck”, take more chances, be more active, and show up more often.
.
⭐️Stay #MOSITIVE

Flex on em
.
Whenever you’re setting out to achieve big things, you’ll have lots of people who will come and tell you all the reasons why your goal is too big, out of reach and blah blah blah.
.
The thing is, those people and their opinions ARE IRRELEVANT to your success.
.
You have the choice to:
.
A) Listen to those people who have absolutely no impact on your success and let your fear of failure and their opinions paralyze you.
.
B) Hit the mute button on those people, put the blinders on and be RELENTLESS in your pursuit. (Ultimately leading to your success)
.
It’s all on you, ALWAYS. So stop pointing fingers.
.
Let people talk, let people have their doubts, it MEANS NOTHING.
.
You have unlimited potential to achieve all things. Have faith, keep persevering and never give up.
.
⭐️Stay #MOSITIVE
.

🚨 405 in da books! Pumped to hit this goal I set out for myself this year. Mini celebration tomorrow with a turkey feast with the fam and some football then back on the grind Friday.
.
It’s good to celebrate your victories but don’t hang out there too long. Keep pursuing more! I’m not going to wait till 2020 to set my next goal. Why waste the month? Neither should you. Forget New Years, make some “End Years” resolutions. Challenge yourself to get moving now.
.
Never thought I’d be able to bench this much when I first started lifting, but here I am. That’s why I love fitness, it’s such a great analogy to life.
.
When you see someone who’s had success and think wow he/she must have something “special” about them you are essentially saying “yeah I’ll never get there cause I don’t have that special something”
.
This is total CRAP! Like @andyfrisella says “There are no super-humans, just humans, and what one man can do, another can do.”
.
So don’t buy into the myth that you’ll never be like “x” because they have that special something. The truth is, they started just like you! We are all given opportunities to become better everyday. It’s up to you to take advantage of them.
.
Keep swinging your axe guys! Don’t wait for 2020 to make shit happen.
.
Shoutout to @_legionofboom for the fresh @1stphorm threads! XL is fitting nicely

Let’s reflect (see what I did there)
.
Thinking back to a few years ago I never thought I’d be able to look in a dressing room mirror and feel semi comfortable, but I do and I’ll tell you why. Although I don’t feel like I am exactly where I want to be, I’ve made it a long way and I realize now the REAL victory is that I understand that I AM IN CONTROL and EVERY STEP I take matters! It’s all about mindset.
.
Remember - every early morning you put in work at the gym (or late night), every conscious choice you make to eat right, every time you choose to take those extra steps or extra flight of stairs, you are creating a new you. Keep going, be persistent and keep swinging your axe, and one day you’ll look back and realize you crushed your original goal, only to be focused on a bigger one!
.
Side note for everyone that voted, I picked the black joggers.
.
⭐️ Stay #MOSITIVE

🚨 Road to 405 continues with a new 385 PR .
🥞 385 felt nice and buttery but I didn’t want to push 405 today. Finished up the push day workout as planned and have my sights set on 405 for Turkey Day.
.
❗️It’s important to warm up properly when attempting a one rep max. It took me a long time to figure out a balance between getting a good warm up and saving energy for the main event.
.
✅Here is what I found works best. Bookmark this and use it the next time you are attempting a one rep max.
.
✏️ Warming up for a one rep max
.
Set 1 
50-60% of 1 rep max attempt for 5 reps 2-3 minute rest
.
Set 2
70% of 1 rep max attempt for 3 reps
2-3 minute rest
.
Set 3
80% of 1 rep max attempt for 1 rep
3-5 minute rest
.
Set 4
90% of 1 rep max attempt for 1 rep
5 minute rest
.
Set 5
One rep max attempt
.
🙏 Hope this helps you guys if you’ve been a bit lost with how to ramp up for a PR attempt.
.
⭐️Stay #MOSITIVE
